BRIEFLY 
Santa Monica-based Tosco Corp. announced that it had acquired the right to buy 
a controlling interest in Seminole Fertilizer Corp. of Bartow, Fla., in a 
$115-million deal that would give Tosco its only non-oil business . . . Donald 
J. Trump said he has acquired from Penthouse International its interest in two 
Atlantic City, N.J., properties known as the Penthouse and Columbus Plaza sites 
. . . Computer Sciences Corp. said it has taken a 9% stake in Inforem Ltd., a 
British company. El Segundo-based CSC said it has an option to buy the rest of 
the company by March, 1990. 
